name: Negligence, World #7
description:
| Negligence |
|"Back then I used to stand up all night thinking about how should one come to an understanding of what failure is and what causes such drastic setbacks in life, the misconception of efforts leading to rewards changes the way you look at matters, it’s funny how you would kill so many living creatures while enjoying a walk in the countryside." - Said the journal.
The boy cognized that chasing light spots would lead him to the right path, worlds after worlds he was pursuing shadows, it made him weak and feeling convulsive. The end was near and what remained was only a new virtual beginning, with no means of ever being final.|

Mixed media digital art.
